OL,3,CHow Natasha's Law could impact the
OL,4,CChannel Islands
OL,6,F"Jersey and Guernsey should adopt
OL,7,FNatasha's Law and other food allergy
OL,8,Fregulations to bring them in line with
OL,9,Fstandards in the UK without delay, to
OL,10,Fgive islanders greater transparency
OL,11,Fabout the foods they buy and eat."
OL,13,FNadim continues to explain why the
OL,14,Fislands should follow the UK, he says:
OL,15,F"This is to avoid any tragedy
OL,16,Fhappening, particularly with visitors
OL,17,Fcoming in from the UK who expect to
OL,18,Fhave the same levels of protection. If
OL,19,Fthey don't, something terrible could
OL,20,Fhappen.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G5/6
